review_blob: Bottle thanks to a random guy at 7venth Sun. Pours gold. Smell is funky. You get the sour smell with hop notes. Def different. I think I like the smell. Taste is okay. Not too sour. Kind of bland. Some barrel notes. Not a lot going on in this one. Good enough to chug by the pool. Ive had better and worse wicked weed beers.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle at the brewery. Pours a nice ruby color. Smell is fruity notes and lots of lime. Taste is dry. Hint of fruits and a lot of lime. Citrus flavor? Doesnt drunk like a typical Saison. Very good. One of the better 7venth Sun beers Ive had.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Ditto.  Everything the guy above me said is true. Its awesome..cigar city does a good job all the time.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cigar City Da Un Beso A La Botella

review_blob: Draft a mellow mushroom. Pours a light orange. Smell is nothing. Mild hops. Taste is the same. Some bitterness with what tastes like old hops. Tastes like it is flat. Being on draft maybe its a little old. I would be interested to try it in a bottle to compare. Not impressed. Wouldnt order it again.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series #10: Dissenter Imperial IPL

review_blob: On tap at the brewery. Pours darker than most browns. Almost black roasty smell. Hints of coffee. Its your average brown. Not nearly as good as the cream and sugar please.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap. Pours orange. Not a lot of smell. Taste is bitter. Not in a good way. Taste like the beer has gone bad. Im not picky, but this isnt good. Its got a bad sour taste to it. Wouldnt order it again. Im a fan of jdub but this is a major disappointed.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap at mellow mushroom in Clearwater. Not much smell. Just some tartness. Its a hazy orange. Cant see through the glass. Decent look. Taste is pretty decent. Not overpowering. You could drink a couple and enjoy yourself. Its a run of the road sour on draft. Nothing fancy. Its good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap at Nolans pub. Pours a dark, cloudy orange. Smell is all citrus and fruit. Not bad. Taste is a lot of hops. Def boozy. Pretty damn good. Gotta make a trip to st Pete soon to try more of their beers.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
On tap at brewery. Very good. Smell is sweet. Taste is all peanut butter. Sweet, strong, very good. Best beer Ive had here along with the gose.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Tap at brewery. Poures dark black. Nice head. Smell is very sweet. Taste is even more sweet. Dark notes, a sugar bomb. But not overly sweet. Couldnt drink more than one. Damn good though.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap at brewery. Pours a light gold. Pretty plain. Not spectacular. Smell is not much either. A little mosaic aroma. The taste is better than expected. Floral, tangy, with a nice bite at the end. Nice hoppyness for a double.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap at brewery. Not much aroma. I dont get any. Pours a cloudy orange. Taste is great. Big on the palate for a session. Fruit notes. Goes down easy. Simcoe hops maybe? Either way. Its one of the better session IPAs I have had in Florida. Better than 7venth suns if you are from the area.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap at the brewery. Pours a dark brown. Smell is very sweet. A lot of coffee and chocolate also. Different form a porter. Smooth, dark chocolate flavor. Lactose. Really easy to drink even when its so hot out. Pretty good. Id get it again.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle poured into. Glass. Get a bourbon smell. Havent really been a fan of big sound. Taste is just as youd expect. The barrel doesnt so much to it. Not worth the money I spent on it.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cigar City Big Sound Scotch Ale - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Pours dark brown. Little head. Smell is dark fruit and bourbon. Some roasted caramel? Taste is smoother than I thought it would be. Bourbon, tangy, a little harsh in a good way. More dried fruit and bourbon. Overall pretty decent.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Pours a dark black with a huge thick tan head. Smell is all espresso. Vanilla notes. Taste is very smooth. More espresso and vanilla. It drinks very easily. Sticky, sweet, and stays with you for a while. I just dont get a lot of rum. But it is still pretty amazing. Not a lot of complaints here.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cigar City Caff Americano Double Stout (Rum Barrel-Aged)

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a nice brown with a nice tan had. Smell is all apple and cinnamon. Pretty much apple pie. Taste is more of the same. Apples, cinnamon, a lot of brandy. Its pretty much like eating an awesome apple pie. Pretty goddamn good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Funky Buddha Muy Bonita - Lairds Apple Brandy Barrel

review_blob: Holy hell. Smells strong. Malty with a big caramel note. Maybe some dark fruits. Smells like a barely wine. Pours a dark golden color. Brown like. Taste is heavy. Hoppy, tart, strong. More like a barley wine than a DIPA. Be ready to sip this. It hits you hard.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: Out of the can. Pours a nice orange. Smell is all citra hops. Tastes great for a session. As expected. Pretty good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On tap. Pours a nice dark brown with a tan head. Smell is hazelnut, coffee, rum, spice. Pretty complex. Taste is very good. Goes down easy. Like an iced coffee with a hint of rum with hazelnut creamer. Pretty awesome.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cycle Fast Breaker - Rum Barrel Hazelnut

review_blob: On tap. Smell is all rum. Comes out black with a nice tan head. Taste is very smooth. A nice balance of the richness and the barrel. Easy to drink for such a strong beer. Comparable to BA Zhukov. Just as good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

2013 on tap. Pours jet black. Nice tan head. Smell of Zhukov with a bourbon nose. Taste is great. The rum goes perfect with the beer. It breaks it down, makes it less thick, and the rum takes over. But not to strong. My favorite Zhukov variant for sure.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cigar City Marshal Zhukovs Imperial Stout - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Bottle. Pours black.  Smells of straight coffee.  Taste is hoppy.  Like drinking iced coffee.  Good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle. Pours a nice golden color. Huge white head. Smell of wheat and hops. A little bit of fruit character. taste is fruit. Goes down smooth. A little beat of wheat in the taste. Maybe a little Brett?? Either way, its pretty good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle. pours a really nice cloudy dark orangeish color. Aroma is all orange peel. Not much else. Pretty good on the palate also. Hoppy. Taste is more orange peel. A little hoppy. Taste more like a nice Pale Ale. But I dont mind it. Good beer on a hot day.
beer_name: Dunedin The Moon Reflects On Hibiscus

review_blob: bottle. Pours a very nice cloudy orange. Aroma is great. Immediate hops. Like a DIPA. Taste is hoppiness in the front. Get some brett in the back end. Very balanced overall. I really like it. Different than other pale ales. Drinks more like a IPA with a nice touch of brett in the back.

Bottle thanks to Beechner224. Pours a very nice dark red color. Aroma is a lot of oak. Some fruitiness. Taste is very tart. oak in the back end. it stays with you for a while. Very good. Drinks easier than the ABV. I like it.
On draft at ccb. Nice grapefruit color. Smell is tart. Not much peach. Goes down smooth with a funky finish. Drinks nice for 6.5. Good beer for a hot day.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Pours a very nice light orange to gold color. Smell is a little funky to me. Some hops with a little sour smell. Taste is dry. Sticks to my tongue. Little hoppy. Not my favorite style but its not terrible.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Pours a dark black. Smell is whiskey and mints. Taste is better than the non BA version. Mint in the front end and whiskey in the back end. I like it a lot. I am glad i traded for this beer. It is great all around..

Bottle share. Smell is all mint to me. Hints of chocolate maybe. Pretty great aroma. Pours a dark black. Nice tan head. Taste is mint, mint, mint. Chocolate a little bit. It is really good. Really smooth for a 10% beer.
Poured from the bottle. Pours a dark black with little head. Smell is very peanut and chocolate. Taste is good. Thin but good. More peanut butter. Id have it again.

Bottle thanks to Beechner224. Pours a dark black with a huge tan head. First smell is straight chocolate. Maybe hints of vanilla? Taste is thick. It coats my mouth. I can still taste it which isnt a bad thing. As it warms up it just get more thick and chocolate. But overall very good. Id drink it more.

Bottle thanks to Beechner224. Pours a dark black with a big tan head. Aroma is not much. I dont get a lot. Maybe a tiny hint of bourbon. Taste is thin, nothing like the Brunch Weasel. This taste a little burnt and thin. One of the few beers where I prefer the non BA version a lot more.
beer_name: Amager / Mikkeller Hr. Frederiksen Vsel Brunch BA

review_blob: On tap at brewery. Pours a orange color with white head. Aroma is hoppy, A little fruity. Taste is very smooth. Cant believe this is 10%. This could be drank all day. very good. Fruity, hoppy, tangy, hops are still present.

On tap at brewery. Pours a cloudy yellow. Aroma is hoppy, Taste is hoppy in the front and some dryness in the back end going down. Pretty interesting. Not used to hoppy saisons, but that is exactly what it is. Pretty dame good.
Draft at Dunedin Brewery. Pours orange with white head. Aroma is hoppy, Taste is more of the same. Nothing special. Just a really good IPA on a hot day.
draft at 7venth Sun.. Pours murky orange, nice head. Aroma is lemon, tart, dry, very nuce... not funky. Really drinkable beer. Id drink this all day.
beer_name: 7venth Sun Yeast Bay Nights (Lochristi Brett Blend)

review_blob: So bad. Thats all I need to say. Smell of awfulness. Taste is even worse.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Smell is pepper.  All pepper. Not good.  So bad.  Is this a joke?  Ive never tasted anything this crazy.  My mouth is on fire. So bad!  Who would buy this?  Unfortunately me.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle thanks to beechner224. Taste is floral. Dry in the back end. Get the fruit all the way through. It was good. Not sure why this is rated so low.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Wicked Weed Royal Cache - Passiflora Blanc

review_blob: Bottle thanks to beechner224. Pours a hazy color and very cloudy. Smells like a typical gose. Taste is an exceptional gose. Couldnt get much better. Its Basically the prototypical summer beer sitting by the pool.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

On draft. Not much aroma. Pours orange. Taste is bitter with a nice hoppiness. Good summer time beer in my opinion. I could drink a few at a time. Not sure why it is rating so low on here.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Draft a wob. Comes out a light golden color. Smell is all hops. Taste is more of the same. Very good. Pretty much everything you want in a nice DIPA.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle at wob. Floral smell. Not much. Light gold color. Taste is smooth, black pepper, kind of bland. Worth trying but nothing special. Not a terrible beer, but not great.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle at wob. Smell of cherries and bourbon. Dark with a little red haze. Taste is very tart. Bourbon and cherries at the back end. Very drinkable. Its pretty damn good.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Wicked Weed Black Angel Cherry Sour

review_blob: Bottle at westchase wob. Pours a dark amber. Cloudy but nice. Smell is all hops. Not much complexity. Taste is boozy as hell. Hops. You can def tell its 12. It doesnt hide. But it is a pretty straight forward triple IPA as far as I can tell. Im good with just one.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Pours a very nice dark red. Smell is all bourbon and cherries. A tiny hint of oak. Pretty awesome. Taste is pretty tart. Bourbon mostly in the front and back end. Just enough cherry. Overall a great beer.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cascade Drie Zwarte Pieten Sang Noir

review_blob: Pours orange. No head. Smell is all coffee. Taste is old coffee with the blonde ale in the back. Doesnt mix well at all. Not a fan. Points for trying a blonde with coffee I guess.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Odd Side Ales Bean Flicker Coffee Blonde

review_blob: Pours gold. Big white head. Smell is mostly humidor. A little sour aroma. The taste is great to me. Typical spur but with the humidor flavor in the back. Never had a humidor sour and dont know of another one. But this is great. Deserves more than a 78.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Cigar City Humidor Series American Sour Ale
